article.headline: Central Florida 74, Stetson 54
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Dexter Lyons and Roberto Morentin combined for 40 points and Marcus Avant pulled down 11 rebounds, leading Central Florida to a 74-54 win over Stetson on Saturday. It was the third straight victory for the Golden Knights (19-4, 14-2 Atlantic Sun), who regained the conference lead by a half-game over Troy State. The loss ended a four-game winning streak for the Hatters (11-12, 9-8). Lyons hit three 3-pointers in the second half and finished with a game-high 23 points, while Morentin scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds. Stetson closed to within 39-34 with 17:07 left in the game, but UCF went on a 7-0 run to push its lead back to double figures. Stetson never got any closer than 10 points the rest of the game. E.J. Gordon finished with 12 points to lead Stetson.
